Currently when you have JIRA and Confluence linked together and you paste in a JIRA link into Confluence, you see the attached image (jira-macro.png). This is a macro that is built into Confluence.

We would like the ability to also have the same functionality developed for Crucible and Confluence so that we can paste in the Crucible link and it does something very similar. This would be extremely useful and a beneficial addition to the Confluence portfolio of plugins.

For example it could display using the same border as the JIRA macro:
{noformat}
If http://crucible.company.com/CRU/CR-123 was pasted in:
CR-123 - Subject - Status

If http://crucible.company.com/CRU/CR-123#c964 was pasted in:
CR-123 - Comment - Status
{noformat}

If I have the wrong place to log this - please let me know or move it elsewhere.

