From time to time in Support, we encounter cases where customers give us all of their logs, only to discover the entirety of their logs have filled up with errors from a full index or something, and we can't see back far enough to troubleshoot the problem.

The default logging behavior for atlassian-confluence.log is to roll them over every 20 MB from atlassian-confluence.log.1 to atlassian-confluence.log.5. Any logs older than that will be removed, ensuring that there are only up to 120 MB of logs at any given time.

While the logging can be changed by adjusting properties in log4j, I propose to simply keep these logs that would otherwise be deleted, but compressed in .zip archive(s). There can still be a maximum size set for the archives, but with compression this should allow us to keep a lot more history.

